.TH LOA-ADD 1 "2026-03-15" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
add \- Interactively add a new item (book or sheet music)
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> add
.SH DESCRIPTION
.TP
Starts a guided prompt for title and type (\fBBook\fR or \fBSheetMusic\fR), then asks matching metadata.
.TP
For sheet music, additional prompts include composer, instrumentation, catalog/work number, key, era/style, difficulty, duration, publisher, and practice status.
.TP
Language is stored as one of: German, English, French, Japanese.
.TP
Type cancel at any prompt to abort.
.TP
Item data is saved immediately after a successful add.
.TP
Duplicate ISBN entries are rejected.
.TP
Duplicate signatures are rejected:
.br
Book -> title+author+language+cover
.br
SheetMusic -> title+composer+instrumentation+catalog/work number+publisher
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> add
.TP
alexandria> (follow prompts and finish with notes)
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1)
.SH AUTHOR
Generated for the Library Of Alexandria project.
